    <div class="left copy">
      <h1><%= @title = "Childrens Chorus" %></h1>
      <p>
	The Children's Chorus is a performing group consisting of young voice students. Students develop skill in group singing and are exposed to a wide variety of arrangements from a diverse range of cultures</p>
	<p>
	Advanced singers aged 6-10 that are proficient in music reading are enrolled in the Chamber Singers group, a select choral organization.
	</p>
	<p>
	The Children's Chorus program is offered tuition-free through the WREACH OUT program, which is generously funded by <a href = "http://www.dcyf.org" target="_blank">DCYF</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="right">
      <h2 class="first">Details</h2>
      <ul class="program-details">
	<li>
	  Registration Fee: $80
	</li>
	<li>
	  Tuition: None
	</li>
	<li>
	  Eligible: Children ages 6-12 residing in San Francisco
	</li>
	<li>
	  When: <br>
	  Chamber Singers: Monday 2:00 pm to 3:30 pm<br>
	  Beginner singers: Tuesday 3:00 pm to 4:00 pm
	</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
